items.title: Getting Started with X-CUBE-BLE1
items.description: The X-CUBE-BLE1 is an expansion software package for STM32Cube. It runs on the STM32 microcontrollers and includes drivers for BlueNRG-MS Bluetooth low energy device. It is built on STM32Cube software technology to ease portability across different STM32 microcontrollers. This video shows how to use the X-CUBE-BLE1 pack in the STM32CubeMX tool.

items.title: Advanced pin assignment and conflict resolution
items.description:
STM32CubeMX offers the possibility to assign each signal of the peripheral mode to a pin, looking for the first free compatible pin.
To resolve the pin conflicts that may occur when some peripheral modes use the same pins, STM32CubeMX attempts to reassign the peripheral mode functions to other pins.

items.title: How to enable TrustZone and start a project with STM32L5
items.description:
Find out more information: http://bit.ly/stm32L5

The STM32L5 is based on Arm Cortex-M33 and TrustZone technology combined with STMicroelectronics security implementation. On your STM32L562E-DK discovery board, TrustZone is disabled (factory setting) and you can develop as on any other STM32 device. This video shows how to enable TrustZone on STM32L562E-DK discovery using STM32CubeProgrammer and create, compile and debug or run a new project with STM32CubeIDE. It also shows how to open an example project delivered in STM32CubeL5 MCU Package, modify, compile and debug or run it. For further information, you can refer to AN5394 and AN5424 application notes.
